one analogy i like is thinking of it as being stuck in a trash compactor with a bunch of other people.
if i have to live in the compactor for a couple of decades but it takes millions of years to crush all of us, i'm not terribly worried; everything i can ever aspire to accomplish will have perished by the time it all ends anyways.
if the compactor crushes us all within 100-150 years, i start struggling with the issue at hand: i may not experience it myself, but my children will, and all i have dedicated my life to is guaranteed to vanish within that time frame. this affects both my state of mind and my actions, and i may start talking to others about it in hopes of finding someone who can convince me that i'm wrong or that there is a way out.
